ge - amount in dispute</strong></th>\n      <th><strong>Tribunal fee</strong></th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£500 or less</td>\n      <td>£50</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£500 to £1,000</td>\n      <td>£70</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£1,000 to £5,000</td>\n      <td>£100</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£5,000 to £15,000</td>\n      <td>£200</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£15,000 or more</td>\n      <td>£350</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Taking the case to a hearing costs £150.</p>\n\n<p>You can pay by postal order or cheque (payable to &lsquo;HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service&rsquo;).</p>\n\n<h2>Help paying costs</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re on benefits, like Income Support, you can ask for help with your fees, using the form below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2968\" title=\"Application for reduction or waiver of fees\" rel=\"external\">Application for reduction or waiver of fees</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Get help and advice</h2>\n\n<p>You can get help and advice from the Leasehold Advisory Service or the Residential Property Tribunal Service:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Leasehold Advisory Service</strong>  </p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://clients.lease-advice.org/Default.aspx\" title=\"Online enquiry form\" rel=\"external\">Online enquiry form</a><br />\n0845 600 3178</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Residential Property Tribunal Service</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>0845 600 3178</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>What happens after you send your appeal</h2>\n\n<p>The tribunal may ask for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>more information - eg a copy of the lease</li>\n  <li>permission to inspect the property</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You may have to go to a hearing with the freeholder.</p>\n\n<p>If there isn&rsquo;t a hearing, the tribunal will ask you to send written evidence.</p>\n\n<p>The tribunal will send you a letter giving its decision (usually within 6 weeks of any hearing).</p>\n\n<h2>If you disagree with the tribunal&rsquo;s decision</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to appeal against the decision to a higher tribunal, called the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber).</p>\n\n<p>To do this, you have to ask the Leasehold Valuation Tribunal for permission to appeal, using the form below:</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><a href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2983\" title=\"Application to the leasehold valuation tribunal for permission to appeal a decision of the tribunal to the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber)\" rel=\"external\">Application to the leasehold valuation tribunal for permission to appeal a decision of the tribunal to the Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must send this form to your local rent assessment panel within 21 days of getting its decision.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Find out more about appealing to the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.justice.gov.uk/guidance/courts-and-tribunals/tribunals/lands/index.htm\" title=\"Lands Tribunal guidance\">Upper Tribunal (Lands Chamber).</a></p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/housing-tribunals/residential-property-tribunal-council-homes-and-park-homes","slug":"residential-property-tribunal-council-homes-and-park-homes","order":3,"title":"Residential Property Tribunal: council homes and park homes","body":"<p>The Residential Property Tribunal can help solve disagreements about:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>council homes</li>\n  <li>park homes (static caravans or mobile homes)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Council homes</h2>\n\n<p>You can appeal to the tribunal if you disagree with a decision about your council home, eg to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>reuse an empty building</li>\n  <li>improve parts of a building</li>\n  <li>demolish or close a building</li>\n  <li>make a property safe</li>\n  <li>restrict how many peo