t Social HomeBuy - a part rent, part buy scheme for council and housing association tenants who can't afford to buy through Right to Buy or Right to Acquire","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>With Social HomeBuy, you buy a share of your council or housing association home and pay rent on the rest of it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>To apply, ask your landlord for an application form. </p>\n\n<h2>Discounts</h2>\n<p>You’ll get a discount of between £9,000 and £16,000 on the value of your home, depending on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>where your home is</li>\n  <li>the size of the share you’re buying</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you want to buy another share in your home later on, you’ll get a discount on that too.</p>\n\n<h2>Buying more of your home later</h2>\n<p>You must buy at least 25% of your home.  You can buy more later, until you own 100%. This is called &lsquo;staircasing&rsquo;. </p>\n\n<p>If you buy more of your home, your rent will go down - because it&rsquo;s based on how much of the property you rent. Your landlord can charge rent of up to 3% of the value of their share of your home, per year.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong>\nYour home is worth £240,000 and you buy a 50% share. Your landlord charges you 3% rent on their 50% share. 3% of £120,000 is £3,600 per year. This works out at £300 per month for you to pay in rent.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Who can&rsquo;t apply</h2>\n<p>You can’t use Social HomeBuy if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you have an <a href=\"/housing-association-homes/types-of-tenancy\" title=\"Housing association homes (Tenancy types)\">assured shorthold tenancy</a></li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re being made <a href=\"/bankruptcy/overview\" title=\"Bankruptcy\">bankrupt</a></li>\n  <li>a court has <a href=\"/council-housing-association-evictions/overview\" title=\"Council and housing association evictions\">ordered you to leave your home</a></li>\n  <li>your landlord is taking action against you for rent arrears, anti-social behaviour or for breaking your tenancy agreement</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Not all local councils or housing associations have joined the scheme. Check with your landlord to find out if they belong to the scheme and whether your home is included.</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Council housing and housing association","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/housing%2Fcouncil-housing-association.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Applying for housing, home ownership schemes and sheltered housing","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=housing%2Fcouncil-housing-association","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/housing/council-housing-association"},"parent":{"title":"Housing and local services","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/housing.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Your legal obligations and rights when renting, buying or owning a home, plus information about Council Tax, what to do if you're homeless and where to get help if you have a housing dispute.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=housing","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/housing"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/right-to-buy-buying-your-council-home.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/right-to-buy-buying-your-council-home","title":"Right to Buy: buying your council home","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-11-23T16:17:49+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/right-to-acquire-buying-housing-association-home.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/right-to-acquire-buying-housing-association-home","title":"Right to Acquire: buying your housing association home","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-11-23T15:00:30+00:00"}]},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/your-rights-to-housing-if-youre-under-18.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/your-rights-to-housing-if-youre-under-18","